# Tailwind + Design Tokens

Compose uses shadcn-svelte's token system. Design tokens map to CSS variables
in `src/app.css`; Tailwind utilities resolve to those variables.

## Tokens over raw colors

- `bg-background`, `bg-card`, `bg-popover`
- `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`
- `border-input`, `border-ring`
- `bg-primary`, `bg-destructive`, `bg-accent`
- `text-primary-foreground`, `text-accent-foreground`

Never reach for `bg-blue-500` or `text-gray-700` — they'll look wrong in dark
mode and inconsistent across the app.

## Spacing

The 4px scale: `gap-1, gap-2, gap-3, gap-4, gap-6, gap-8`. No arbitrary
values like `gap-[7px]`. If a spacing decision can't be expressed in the
scale, raise it — the scale is probably wrong.

## Dark mode

Class-based (`dark:` prefix). Tokens already auto-switch — you rarely need
explicit dark mode classes. If you do, the usual suspect is an image or
SVG that needs an inverted variant.

## `cn()` for class merging

Use the `cn()` helper from `$lib/cn` — wraps `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`:

```svelte
<div class={cn('rounded-md border p-4', archived && 'opacity-60', className)} />
```

This handles conflicts correctly: a consumer passing `p-2` will override the
default `p-4`.

## Typography plugin

For long-form text (note bodies, MDX), use the `prose` classes from
`@tailwindcss/typography`:

```svelte
<article class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert max-w-prose">
  {@html note.html}
</article>
```

## Don't

- Don't use raw color palettes from Tailwind (`bg-red-500`, `text-gray-900`)
- Don't use `@apply` in `<style>` blocks — utilities in markup only
- Don't scatter `dark:` variants across components when a token already handles it
- Don't write new CSS variables in `app.css` without updating the shadcn token spec
- Don't use arbitrary values (`h-[73px]`) — if the value isn't in the scale, the design is off
